                                    <h3 class="green1">For 4 years old</h3>
                                    <p class="darkBlue">
                                        Your child must be 4 years of age before 30 April
                                    </p>
                                    <p class="darkBlue">
                                        They are also known as <strong>“Funded Kindergarten”</strong>. The Victorian government helps by providing funding to the services that contribute to the cost of running the program. This helps the parents to keep the fees of your four year old kindergarten as low as possible.
                                        Most 4 year old kindergarten programs are offered for 15 hours a week.
                                    </p>
                                </div>

                                <div>
                                    <h3 class="pink">Did you know?</h3>
                                    <p class="darkBlue">
                                        The Victorian Government subsidises fees for some children so they can attend kindergarten for free or at low cost in the year before they start primary school,usually when they are four years old.

                                    </p>
                                </div>
                                <div>
                                    <h3 class="green1">Is your child eligible?</h3>
                                    <p class="darkBlue">
                                        Your child is eligible if they:<br /><br />
                                        1.are a triplet or quadruplet<br /><br />
                                        2.hold (or have a parent or guardian who holds) a Commonwealth Health Card <br /><br />
                                        3.hold (or have a parent or guardian who holds) a Refugee or Asylum Seeker visa (200-204, 786 or 866)
                                        <br /><br />
                                        4.Bridging visas for any of the above Refugee or Asylum Seeker visas
                                        <br /><br />
                                        In case your family or child has a humanitarian or refugee visa listed by the Department of Immigration and Border Protection which might not be included in the list above,
                                        your child may still be eligible for Kindergarten fee subsidy.
                                        Please ask your child’s kindergarten educator or service manager if you think your child may be eligible for a fee subsidy.


                                    </p>
                                </div>
                                <div>
                                    <h3 class="pink">Your child can attend two years of Kindergarten only when:</h3>
                                    <p class="darkBlue">
                                        In exceptional circumstances when your child displays developmental delays in few learning areas - the child’s kindergarten teacher can apply for an additional year that might be needed for the child only after the discussion with the family and Preschool Field Officer.

                                        The second year will help the child learn and achieve better at kindergarten and prepare the child to go to school.Families eligible children must apply for an exemption from school if the child is turning six at any time in their second year of kindergarten attendance.

                                    </p>
                                </div>
                                <div>
                                    <h3 class="darkBlue"><a href="https://www.education.vic.gov.au/parents/child-care-kindergarten/Pages/kindergarten-programs.aspx">More information</a></h3>

                                </div>

