                                    <h3 class="green1">
                                        Public or Private which one to choose?
                                    </h3>
                                    
                                    <p class="darkBlue">
                                        As a migrant parent it can be difficult to choose between government based kindergartens and privately owned kindergartens.
                                        Let's find out how Public & Private Kindergartens differ from each other
                                    </p>
                                </div>

                                <div>
                                    <h3 class="pink1">Public Kindergartens.</h3>
                                    <p class="darkBlue">
                                        In public schools, the curriculum is typically the same for all students which focuses on core subjects.
                                        This can be a solid foundation for beginning an education for children of all learning levels.
                                        Usually government owned facilities have more intake capacity but they sometimes face shortage of staff because public kindergartens have less control over staffing.This acts as a roadblock
                                        for children to get personalised attention.Public kindergartens usually have older infrastructure but they have a stronger focus on educational philosophy.
                                        These schools specifically focus on the moral, civic and behavioral development in addition to the intellectual development and academic learning.
                                        Teachers working in public school are required to hold all the state licenses and meet all the criteria to serve the students with special learning methods.

                                    </p>
                                </div>
                                <div>
                                    <h3 class="green1">Highlights of Public Kindergartens</h3>
                                    <p class="darkBlue">
                                        1.Considerably less school fees.<br /><br />
                                        2.Parents can avail child care subsidy provided by the Victorian government.<br /><br />
                                        3.Teachers and staff are certified<br /><br />
                                        4.Usually older facilities.<br /><br />
                                        5.Class sizes are generally larger.<br /><br />
                                        6.Admissions to preschools may usually be governed by catchment area.<br /><br />
                                        7.Not religious.<br /><br />
                                        8.Estimated cost of child education through the public system is $66,320. <br /><br />
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                                <div>
                                    <h3 class="pink1">Private Kindergartens</h3>
                                    <p class="darkBlue">
                                        Private Kindergartens can offer your child customised curriculum and a wide range of tailored programs you can choose from depending upon your child’s needs.
                                        They can offer specialised programs and give personalised attention to every child as the intake capacity is low as compared to public kindergartens. Private preschools have full control and authority over staffing.
                                        Children are encouraged to take up their area of interest where they get personalised attention as class size is small with lower student to teacher ratio.
                                        They offer better infrastructure and larger classrooms as they are independent bodies whose funding is not controlled by the government.Private kindergartens are expensive.
                                        If you are religious, private kindergartens can simulate an environment for your child that is more likely to reflect your values and instill deeper understandings of your choden faith.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                                <div>
                                    <h3 class="green1">
                                        Highlights of Private Kindergartens
                                    </h3>
                                    <p class="darkBlue">
                                        1.Higher school fees in comparison.<br /><br />
                                        2.No child care subsidy.<br /><br />
                                        3.Modern Infrastructure.<br /><br />
                                        4.Personalised attention to children.<br /><br />
                                        5.Low intake capacity.<br /><br />
                                        6.Admission procedure is different from public Kindergartens.<br /><br />
                                        7.Religious.<br /><br />
                                        8.Estimated cost of child education through the private system in the city $475,342.
                                        <br /><br />
                                    </p>
                                </div>

                            </div>
